'''Bikie''' is an [[Australian English|Australian]] term for a [[motorcyclist]], but which also carries connotations of gang affiliation - it thus has the same meaning as the [[United States|American]] term [[biker]]. While many of the groups and mores of Australian bikie culture are the same as, and indeed imported from, the U.S., there are inevitably some differences too. Sometimes bikies get confused with the term bikers. Some bikie gangs that are well known in Australia are: Finks, Hells Angels, Gypsy Jokers, Bandidos, Rebels, Outlaws and Coffin Cheaters.



